		<body>
			<!--<p>EHRI-DR-19430316-IT</p>
      <p>Report from the consul in Skopje, Roberto Venturini, on 16 March 1943 for the legation of
        Sofia. The report was sent to the Italian Foreign Ministry in Rome on 23 March 1943 together
        with a report from the Consul in Bitolia.</p>
      <p/>
      <p>[Handwritten notation:] Copy</p>
      <p/>
      <p>R. Consulate of Italy, Skopje</p>
      <p>Addressed to the R. Legation of Italy, Sofia</p>
      <p>Cable No. 417/92</p>
      <p>Classified</p>
      <p>Position A 71/I</p>
      <p/>
      <p>Skopje, 16th March 1943, Year XXI</p>-->
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-DR-19430316-IT_01.jpg"/>
			<p>Re: Measures against the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Israelites</term> of
				Macedonia.</p>
			<p/>
			<p>At 12 midnight of the 10th inst., while troops were blocking the streets of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/785842/skopje.html"
					>Skopje</placeName>, groups of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1120" type="subject">policemen</term>
				began to knock at the door of the homes of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject"
					>Israelite</term> families asking them to pack a limited amount of baggage as they were to be taken to a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration camp</term> set up in the <ref
					target="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-jewishcouncil-organisation-jmp-36?dlid=eng">warehouses</ref> of the
				tobacco depository and in the surrounding, fenced-in land. At 6 pm on the 11th the street blockade was lifted and 5,000 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> had already been taken to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration camp</term>, while the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-641" type="subject">hunt</term> for the few who had managed to hide or who
				were roaming the countryside intending to cross into <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/783754/republic-of-albania.html"
					>Albania</placeName> was continuing. Other similar police operations were under way at the same time in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/792578/bitola.html">Bitola</placeName> and in other <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/718075/north-macedonia.html">Macedonian</placeName> towns, leading to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Israelite</term> there being taken to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/785842/skopje.html">Skopje</placeName>, where the number of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-618" type="subject">concentrated people</term> has now risen to over
				9,000. The lengthy examination of their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-621" type="subject"
					>documents</term> and of their baggage and the painstaking body searches will be followed, reportedly within a few days, by <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">deportation</term> to a far-away Country, that it is
				believed will be <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName> for the majority and for
				some perhaps <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2802361/kingdom-of-belgium.html">Belgium</placeName> or <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-places-place-jmp-220">Germany</placeName>.</p>
			<p>It has been a blanket action both as regards people and as regards <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887"
					type="subject">property</term>: even <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term>
				of extremely advanced age or with a serious health condition have been forced to leave their homes and were taken to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> on rough carts, while their homes with all
				their contents were declared State property and even what little they had been allowed to take with them was later further restricted.
				They have each been left with only the oldest <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject"
					>garment</term> and the oldest shoes <pb n="1" facs="EHRI-DR-19430316-IT_02.jpg"/>they had brought with them, and the search for
				gold and money about the persons of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-618" type="subject">concentrated
					people</term> has enabled officials, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1120" type="subject"
					>policemen</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">soldiers</term> to walk
				off with all they could still lay their hands on: even scraps of soap, used toothbrushes and almost empty tubes of toothpaste have
				been taken away from these unfortunate people who may truly be said to have be left with only their eyes to weep with.</p>
			<p>Added to the worries about their entirely uncertain future and to the pain for the total loss of all <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887" type="subject">property</term>, the 9,000 people about to be <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">deported</term> face absolutely unnecessary hardships
				that are inflicted on them due to lack of foresight or to mere brutality. The most basic sanitary facilities, which at first were
				lacking almost entirely, are only now beginning to work but still only inadequately, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-832" type="subject">food</term> is very scarce and
				unsuitable (during the first days they gave out, even to babies only a few months old, some thin bean slops without any bread), the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-286" type="subject">guards</term> seize on any
				pretext to use with sadistic force the whips they carry, while the crowding of all sorts of people within a cramped space renders rest
				all but impossible. The tragic but logical consequence of all this are suicides ‚Äì as far as I know there have been at least three so
				far ‚Äì and, particularly among women, instances of hysterical agitation bordering on insanity.</p>
			<p>According to what <orgName ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_bulgarians">Bulgarians</orgName> are saying, the total elimination of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Israelite</term> from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/718075/north-macedonia.html">Macedonia</placeName> has been requested by <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-places-place-jmp-220">Germany</placeName> for military reasons: there can be
				no doubt, however, that they have made excellent, huge gains out of it, and that in carrying it out the have displayed the most total
				disregard for even the most basic humanitarian principles. I do not hesitate to claim that there are very few people who, being
				present in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/785842/skopje.html">Skopje</placeName> on 11th March and having seen the manner in
				which the Israelite families were being taken to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject"
					>concentration camp</term> and having then heard how they were being treated, have not felt a sense of pity for those thus
				stricken and of deep condemnation of the Bulgarian authorities responsible for this and for their agents.</p>
			<p>As for the Italian Israelite Modiano family]and the families of Israelites who are Albanian nationals in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/785842/skopje.html">Skopje</placeName> and have been taken to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration camp</term>, presumably 9 families with
				approx. 25 members, I have already reported with telegram no. 409/88 of the 14th March inst. and I intend to report further.</p>
			<p>The R. Consul <persName ref="#ehri_dr_Venturini_Roberto">Roberto Venturini</persName></p>
